Legal frameworks: 
    Key regulations:GDPR,HIPAA,PCI-DSS
Why compliance matters-Avoiding fines,legal protection,loss of trust,competitive advantage

GDPR:Genaral Data Protection Regulation
    focus-Data privacy and protection of Europeans' data
    Companies that breach this rule have 72 hours to report to GDPR and face penalties up to 20 million Euros or 4% of global turnover,whichever is higher

HIPAA: Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act
      It applies to anyone handling US patient health data.
      Privacy rule: controls who can see  PHI (Protected Health Information)
      Penlties upto 1.5 million dollars per violation type as breach rule
PCI-DSS: Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard
        Applies to any organization that processes credit/debit card data to prevent payment fraud, encrypt card holder data,etc
penalty if breached: 5000 to 100000 dollars per month + loss of ability to process cards
